About the last task - it was quite intuitive. What I valued the most when deciding if an offer should be accepted was the agreement between the proposals of P1 and P2, and the distribution of the money as equally as possible. At the beginning I felt more inclined to decline an offer if P1 offered a low value and P2 offered a high one (or vice-versa) as it didn't feel it would lead to a fair distribution between the three. As the questions progressed I started to feel less inclined to decline offers that could be a bit uneven but that would at least bring a bit of money to all players. The concepts of even sharing and fairness were also the key guides to my answers on the tasks about the distribution of resources.
